    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Carpenters of old Spain who practiced rough woodwork without decoration or smooth finishes. The wood they worked with served as a base for the more refined and detailed work of the 'carpintero de lo blanco.'</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
